RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 81. Claiming Purse 51000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $23,500, allowed 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KERICS BEAUTY settled on the rail in the middle of the field down the backstretch, began picking up rivals inside with five sixteenths remaining, angled out to the four path for the stretch drive and wore down the loose frontrunner in deep stretch for the win. SEATTLE CAUSEWAY took command from the start, set a soft pace taking the field down the backstretch, opened up turning for home and was caught late just missing out in the end. BEQUIA tracked the pacesetter in the two path going into the first turn, was outside keeping a close eye on the frontrunner with a half remaining, was slowly gaining on the leader through the lane between horses but could not find more in deep stretch to pose a threat for the win. TARA LUNA travelled in mid pack throughout, was urged on the final turn and showed some late interest picking up the pieces in the stretch drive to get a minor role. HALLANVAARA was allowed to settle near the back into the first turn, saved ground through the backside, continued to skim the rail on the far turn and passed a weary runner down the lane. CHROME'S ANGEL had a good position tracking the leaders outside under a snug hold down the back straight, was ridden to go after the frontrunners midpoint on the far turn, offered little response and faded in upper stretch. MUM'S THE WORD trailed the pack in the early stages of the race, was urged with three furlongs left to run, lost touch with the field on the far turn and galloped to the wire.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 2 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 32800. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $9,500, allowed 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUNGLE TIGRESS had a good position watching the top pair at the half, rallied up the fence midway on the turn, shifted out three wide turning for home and was full of run down the lane to win comfortably at the wire. EYE GOT IT GOOD hopped at the start to be near the rear down the back straight on the rail, advanced inside with three furlongs left to run, split foes angling out to the three path at the quarter marker and closed belatedly to be second best at the finish. CASTLETON tracked on the rail in the second flight in the early stages, kept pace with the leaders running on the turn and showed late stretch energy inside to finish up well to capture the show award. BIG BANG BLUE had a slow start to be near the back in the beginning stages of the race, could still see most of the field racing on the turn and found her best stride late finishing up well to get a small share of the prize crossing the line. FOREST VIXEN took command from the start, put away an early outside foe midway on the turn, was collared by the winner in upper stretch and stopped in the final seventy yards losing a few positions nearing the wire. GENTLE SEAS travelled outside in the middle stalking the leaders, offered a mild run three wide at the three furlong marker and stalled in the six path in upper stretch. SAKE AND SUSHI pressed the issue two wide down the backside, was scrubbed on the keep pace up front three eighths from the prize and yielded turning for home. HI AST POWER was void of early speed outside to trail at the half, made little headway running on the turn and was not a factor in the stretch drive. SPIRIT O'TIPPERARY settled in the middle of the pack in the beginning, could not match strides with rivals through the turn, was pushed out some entering the stretch and faded at the furlong marker.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORTYFIVESEVENTY tracked in the two path down the backside, made an early move to get a good position entering the turn, contested for the lead outside five sixteenths from home, battled three wide with rivals on either side at the top of the lane and stubbornly prevailed with a good finish the final furlong. BEDAZZLE ME was content to trail the field down the back straight, took up the chase on the rail three furlongs out, waited patiently for a seam inside through the turn, burst through four wide to bid between foes in upper stretch but was outkicked in the final eighth and had to settle for the runners up share. FRIENDS FOR LIFE tracked four wide outside horses at the half, travelled three wide on the turn keeping pace with the top pair outside, was pushed out widest to the five path turning for home and finished evenly in the stretch to be a clear third. TIPSY MOON led the field down the backstretch, was headed outside by the eventual winner three furlongs from the finish, was battling stubbornly on the rail at the top of the lane and gave way in the final furlong. UMNEYAAT tracked three wide between rivals down the backside, was shuffled back to trail this compact field at the three eighths pole and could not find another gear at the quarter marker to pose a threat for the stretch drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 4 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 83. Waiver Claiming Purse 40200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Consi dered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOXER BRIEF settled off the pace, fanned seven wide into upper stretch, made a sustained rally while drifting in a bit in mid- to late-stretch and edged past late. SWATH moved forward and clear to set the pace, soon faced pressure from an outside rival up the backstretch and on the turn, came out a bit turning for home, kicked clear by mid-stretch, drifted out just a bit soon after, was outkicked by the winner but a clear second. LOMAKI FORCE angled in after the start settling at the back, saved some ground on the turn, came out in upper stretch for room, had to alter outside runners near the sixteenth pole and kicked on to just get up for third. VICTORY MARCH broke a step slowly and in a bit tight, pulled through between rivals to a forward position, pressed the leader two to three wide into the turn, floated four wide into upper stretch, evened out and lost show honors late. LOVE THE GAME bobbled at the break, raced off the pace inside, angled five wide into the stretch, kept on evenly late. BODIE moved forward inside to track the leading pair, saved ground early on the turn, shifted four wide coming out of that bend, took aim on the leader, ran on somewhat evenly but steadied on heels about the sixteenth. GUNGI tossed the head and was in tight at the start, raced in the back half of the field off the rail, was never near enough to threaten. STUBBORN STREAK raced outside foes toward the rear and failed to menace. NOVA FOLHA stalked the leaders from outside into the turn, fanned six wide into the stretch, dropped back and faded. HIP TO YOUR TRICKS was quite hard to load, steadily retreated. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF BODIE AGAINST SWATH ALLEGING INTERFERENCE NO ACTION WAS TAKEN AND RESULTS TO STAND AS IS.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: OCTOBER FROST was bumped into a rival at the start then bounced around between foes a few strides after, shifted in and had to tap on the brakes a bit early on the first turn racing in behind rivals inside, settled soon after, shifted five wide beginning past the five-sixteenths to the top of the stretch, engaged the leader putting a head in front a furlong out, edged away late. NONNO'S LITTLE BOY was caught outside four wide into the first turn off the leader, advanced with those runners on the pacesetter four to five deep up the backstretch racing just off the latter into the far turn, moved to the fore nearing the quarter pole taking a narrow lead, was challenged near the eighth pole, yielded only grudgingly late. TRINITY PARK settled off the pace shifting in just outside a rival two to three wide early, raced in behind off the leaders up the backstretch, came out six wide for the drive and kicked on late to secure show honors. PRINCE OF AYRSHIRE was forced out and into a rival at the start then exchanged a bump soon after, raced forwardly three wide then advanced on the leader midway up the backstretch taking closer order four deep and between runners, dropped back from the seven-sixteenths, fanned eight wide for the drive and kept on late to improve position. SPRING MOUNTAIN was bumped at the start then bumped a rival soon after, moved forward pulling keenly to draw clear and shift in setting the pace just off the rail, was pressured nearing the half, weakened in the stretch. BET N WIN veered out at the break brushing the gate and forcing a rival out, had forward position but content to rate off the early lead inside, advanced outside that one up the backstretch to press from the nine-sixteenths, bid between runners coming to the three-eighths, had a narrow lead briefly on the turn but was overtaken by the quarter pole, had no extra for the drive. MISTER MESEEKS was unhurried at the rear racing inside and never near enough to threaten.

LITTLE DOMI stalked in the middle of the pack on the rail, advanced on the fence through the turn, shifted outside three deep off fading runners as they turned for home and could not make an impact to the finish. AIR FORCE RESERVE forced the issue up front between rivals at the half, continued to fight for the top spot with five sixteenths to go and stopped in upper stretch. CHICAGO FREDDY started a touch slow to begin, stalked near the back of the field at the half, could not get involved running on the turn and was a non factor in the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THREE SONNY SIDEUP had a short lead in the early going, scooted away from the chasing rival at the five sixteenths marker, was headed outside by multiple challengers at the furlong pole and determinedly dug in to win the nod for the narrow victory at the line. MORSTACHY'S was allowed to settle trailing the field down the backstretch, began to pick up horses outside with three furlongs left to run, showed a good burst of speed circling five wide at the quarter pole to loom the threat in upper stretch and stalled the final sixteenth. RENEGADE SERENADE was two deep near the rear at the half mile marker, made little impression running through the turn and could not reach contention down the lane. CANDY STREET travelled near the rear on the rail in the early going, advanced inside at the half, looked good waiting behind the winner for a seam at the quarter marker and came up empty in the drive to the line.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 72. Waiver Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DO THE GRIDDY pressured the lead outside off the frontrunners flank with four furlongs to go, was gaining three wide at the furlong marker while never switching leads in the stretch and began to edge away in the final strides. PIDIN set the fractions in the early parts of the race, still led the way at the top of the stretch, continued to fight on with an eighth remaining and gave way grudgingly very late. TORY'S HOLIDAY broke out to start, sat off the contesting pair only a few lengths behind into the turn, angled out to split rivals four wide turning for home and finished up with run to just miss getting up for the place award. BOSTON BAY was in a good position sitting behind the engaging duo at the three furlong marker, found a seam on the fence straightening out for the drive, lost his path at the sixteenth pole, shifted out some and held on for a minor role in the end. HARPER CITY was off slowly to begin, settled on the rail in midfield down the back straight, crept up the rail through the turn, angled out to the three path at the furlong marker and offered a good finish in the end to be beaten not that far for it all in the end. TAYBO had a good spot tracking the top pair three wide at the half, was coaxed for more run midway on the turn, turning for home was in with a chance five wide and finished up evenly in the last eighth. ARAMOS was bumped at the start, stalked four deep at the half, travelled four wide outside horses on the turn, shifted out in mid stretch to the seven path and closed the gap between him and the leaders in the late stages of the race. STORMIN DAVE was situated near the back in the early stages of the race, saved ground on the turn, chose to shift five wide turning for home and never threatened but showed interest taking closer order to the leaders at the finish. I'M NO SLEEPY JOE was bumped on the break to trail the field in the beginning, could not get into gear throughout the turn and was never a menace finishing down the stretch. QUIET SPEED settled in the middle of the pack three wide down the backside, was hard ridden three wide at the three furlong marker, could not quicken with rivals and tired at the top of the lane. IT'S ME MARIO was three wide with runners on either side in mid pack, made little change in position throughout the turn and had nothing to show running in the stretch.
